I need to identify and extract the specific line items and value of expense in the statement of profit or loss and other comprehensive income from the balance sheet.

Looking at the provided balance sheet, I need to find expense-related items. In accounting, accumulated depreciation represents the total amount of depreciation expense recorded for an asset since its acquisition. It's a contra-asset account that reduces the value of fixed assets and represents an expense over time.

From the balance sheet:
- The "Accumulated Depreciation" line item shows an initial value of 0.00 on 2023-12-31
- The "Accumulated Depreciation" line item shows an end value of 45748.43 on 2024-01-27

This accumulated depreciation represents the depreciation expense that has been recognized during this period.
